\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 NGSPICE Commands
\b0\fs24 \
\

\b 1)
\b0  To open the tool and read file in shell, write: 
\f1\b\fs28 ngspice file_name.sp
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\

\b 2)
\b0  To write the raw file of a circuit: 
\f1\b\fs28 ngspice -b lab1.sp -r lab1.raw
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\

\b 3)
\b0  To write the raw file for each specific part, you need to write the following commands while the NGSPICE is open:\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural
\cf0 \ul \ulc0 Command A\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 wrdata ac db(Node_1) db(Node_2) ...
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
\ul Command B\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 wrdata tran v(Node_1) v(Node_2) ...
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
\ul Command C\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 wrdata fft v(Node)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
\ul Command in Terminal\ulnone : 
\f1\b\fs28 ngspice -b File_Name.sp
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
