\b0 : In each \ul output file\ulnone  that is a \ul row vector\ulnone , all of the Odd numbered columns refer to the values of \ul function argument\ulnone  (e.g. Time) and all of the Even numbered columns refer to the values of \ul function output \ulnone (e.g. Voltage of Node).\
\

\b 4)
\b0  To draw the 
\b FFT Plot
\b0  using MATLAB, write the following commands in its terminal:\
\

\f1\b\fs28 fft = importdata('fft.data')
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\

\f1\b\fs28 frequency = fft(:,1)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\

\f1\b\fs28 real = fft(:,2)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\

\f1\b\fs28 img = fft(:,3)
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\

\f1\b\fs28 semilogx(frequency,20*log10(real+i*img))
\f0\b0\fs24 \
\
